This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and classification of text data. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it focuses on clickbait in social media. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with identifying relevant information from text data. The paper also makes use of machine learning techniques, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the impact of clickbait on user experience.
